hyphae from context.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="tubes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Tubes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
Generative hyphae thin- to slightly thick-walled, rarely branched, subparallel along the tubes to loosely interwoven, 2.5-3.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diam. Cystidia and cystidioles absent. Basidia clavate to barrel-shaped, with four sterigmata and a basal clamp connection, 13-14.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-5.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
; basidioles of similar shape to basidia, but smaller.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="basidiospores">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Basidiospores.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
Ellipsoid, hyaline, thin-walled, smooth, often with one or more guttules, CB-, IKI-, (3.8-)3.9-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.7-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, L = 4.09 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, W = 2.86 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, Q = 1.43 (n = 30/1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. C. Dai, Chao G. Wang &amp; Vlasak" authorityYear="2021" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Bjerkandera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bjerkandera ecuadorensis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ecuadorensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Bjerkandera ecuadorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by grey to dark-brown pore surface, small pores (7-9 per mm), hyaline to yellowish-brown generative hyphae, and ellipsoid basidiospores measuring 3.9-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.7-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. C. Dai, Chao G. Wang &amp; Vlasak" authorityYear="2021" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Bjerkandera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bjerkandera ecuadorensis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ecuadorensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Bjerkandera ecuadorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="B. minispora" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="minispora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">B. minispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having pinkish-buff to buff pileal surface and round to angular pores (6-9 per mm), but the latter has buff-yellow pore surface and smaller basidiospores (3.1-4.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Bjerkandera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bjerkandera adusta" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="adusta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Bjerkandera adusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="B. ecuadorensis" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ecuadorensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">B. ecuadorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having grey to dark-brown pore surface, distinct sterile margin, but the former has short-cylindric to subellipsoid and bigger basidiospores (4.5-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ryvarden, L" journalOrPublisher="Synopsis Fungorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 431" refId="B34" refString="Ryvarden, L, Melo, I, 2017. Poroid fungi of Europe (2nd edn.). Synopsis Fungorum 37: 1 - 431" title="Poroid fungi of Europe (2 nd edn.)." volume="37" year="2017">Ryvarden and Melo 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
